05394nam a22009255i 9783110625318DE-B159720230127011820.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230127t20202020gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831106253187 a10.1515/97831106253182doi  a(DE-B1597)501376  a(OCoLC)1178770345  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aLIT0041902bisacsh04a820.9/3531 aBarton, Roman Alexander, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Making of the Sympathetic Imagination :bTransformations of Sympathy in British Eighteenth-Century Philosophy and Fiction /cRoman Alexander Barton. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (X, 210 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aTransformationen der Antike ,x1864-5208 ;v61  aDissertationcHumboldt-Universität zu Berlind2018.00tFrontmatter -- tPreface -- tTable of Contents -- t1. INTRODUCTION -- t2. SYMPATHY RENDERED MORAL -- t3. SYSTEMS OF SYMPATHY -- t4. FROM ETHICS TO POETICS OF SYMPATHY -- t5. NARRATING SYMPATHY & SYMPATHETIC NARRATION -- t6. SYMPATHY LOST AND REGAINED -- tBIBLIOGRAPHY -- tINDEX OF NAMES -- tINDEX OF SUBJECTS0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aHow is it that we feel with fictional characters and so approve or disapprove of their actions? For many British Enlightenment thinkers writing at a time when sympathy was the pivot of ethics as well as poetics, this question was crucial. Asserting that the notion of the sympathetic imagination prominent in Romantic criticism and poetry originates in Moral Sentimentalism, this study traces the emergence of what became a key concept of intersubjectivity. It shows how, contrary to earlier traditions, Francis Hutcheson and his disciples successively established the imagination rather than reason as the pivotal faculty through which sympathy is rendered morally effective. Writing at the interface of ethics and poetics, Adam Smith, Lord Kames and others explored the sympathetic imagination as a means of both explaining emotional reader response and discovering moral distinctions. As a result, the sentimental novel became the sight of ethical controversy. Arguing against the dominant view of research which claims that the novel of sensibility is mostly uncritically sentimental, the book demonstrates that it is precisely in this genre that the sympathetic imagination is sceptically assessed in terms of its literary and moral potential.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 4aAntike /Rezeption. 4aEnglische Aufklärung. 4aImagination. 4aSympathie. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aBritish Enlightenment.  aImagination.  aSentimentalism.  aSympathy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020 Englishz978311070483908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831106241820 cprintz978311062401440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311062531840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110625318423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110625318/original  a978-3-11-065906-1  De Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCb2020  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus D